        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:45AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 645 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Shawnee, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shawnee, Seminole, Tecumseh, McLoud, Pink, Maud, Earlsboro, Bowlegs,
Johnson, Brooksville, Dale, Little, Bethel Acres, and Harjo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
